If it is not impeachable for a president to abuse his power to win an election, then nothing is impeachable. My vote to impeach President Trump will be a vote to protect our democracy, and to honor my oath to defend our Constitution against all enemies, foreign and domestic.

Let’s be clear about what is at stake: The survival of our democracy. President Trump abused his power and risked America’s security in hopes of bolstering his own re-election chances. Given his record, he is likely to keep doing so unless he is impeached and removed from office.

I will take no joy in voting to impeach President Trump, but our democracy & Constitution demand it. He used his power & taxpayer dollars to pressure a foreign country into attacking one of his American election rivals. He also obstructed Congress's investigation of his conduct. https://twitter.com/latimes/status/1205556240681750536 …
